					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Allow me to interject quickly for a moment here.  I would like to ask (and know) how much more difficult would NES game development be if you were to make your game for a more advanced mapper?  I don't think any homebrew games go above anything higher than UNROM, and if they do, they must be relatively few.  Is the reason why more advanced mappers are ignored is because the games don't need them, or they're harder to work with?  What about something as grand as the MMC5, would that be tricky to work with?  And while on the subject, would it be possible to combine features of mappers?  For example, making an MMC5 derivative where it uses Namco-163 audio instead of two extra squares and a PCM channel?</div>

