					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">OneCrudeDude wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Speaking of scanline stuff, supposedly the DPCM channel could be used as a makeshift scanline counter, or something to that extent.  Maybe it was an IRQ counter.  Did any games ever do that, or was it a mostly unused feature/trick?  Would that even be useful when you finally get it to work?</div><br />Bee 52, an unlicensed game from Codemasters, uses the DPCM IRQ as a wannabe scanline IRQ. IRQ happens during scanlines 162..164, and a sprite 0 hit is used at Y=167 (scanline 168) to stabilize the timing. Inbetween those scanlines they read the controller, presumably because it's the one place where they know DPCM samples can't corrupt the controller reads.</div>

					
