					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">OneCrudeDude wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">that has seamless 8 way scrolling like Gauntlet</div><br />Gauntlet's way of doing 8 way scrolling doesn't take more than 5 minutes to implement: it &quot;cheats&quot; by using 4-screen mirroring (extra memory for nametables on cart) and the levels never span more than 4 nametables.<br /><br />But you are correct, there are many portions in a NES game that can be reused from game to game: map scrolling, compression, audio, sprite rendering, etc etc.</div>

					
